                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 294/82: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-29T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. Reference my despatch number 1906, May 19th, relative costs of Army of
                    Occupation. I am in receipt of note from Foreign Office dated to-day stating
                    that French suggestion that Allied representatives in Paris should be charged
                    with examining the question has been accepted by the other Governments and the
                    French Government consequently intends to call meeting as soon as possible. Copy
                    and translation will be forwarded by next pouch.<note n="68" xml:id="d190fn68"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
